# PR explain pages on Netlify

Every pull request needs a **player-facing HTML description** deployed to Netlify — not just Markdown/HTML in the GitHub PR body.

## Pattern (matches existing sites)

1. Write / update `netlify-site/index.html` in the PR-38 explain style (Press Start 2P + VT323, pill, TL;DR card, What changed, How to try it, Verification, PR link).
2. Create a Netlify site named `pet-village-pr-{N}-explain` (e.g. `pet-village-pr-46-explain`).
3. Deploy the folder:
   ```sh
   npx netlify deploy --prod --dir=netlify-site --site=<site-id>
   ```
4. Put the live URL in the GitHub PR body (short summary + link is enough).

Examples already live:
- https://pet-village-pr-38-explain.netlify.app
- Sibling repos use the same `*-pr-{N}-explain` naming

## GitHub PR body

Keep the GitHub description short. Prefer linking the Netlify explain page:

```markdown
Explain: https://pet-village-pr-46-explain.netlify.app

## Summary
- …
```

Do **not** treat the GitHub body as the primary HTML artifact — that lives on Netlify.
